{% set blockExample %}<code data-math
  data-mathml="<math display='block'><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mo>-</mo><mi>b</mi><mo>&pm;</mo><msqrt><msup><mi>b</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>a</mi><mi>c</mi></msqrt></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>a</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>">
  x = \frac{-b \pm \sqrt{b^2 - 4ac}}{2a}
</code>{% endset %}

{% set inlineExample %}<p>The area is
  <code data-math="inline"
    data-mathml="<math><mi>&pi;</mi><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math>">
    \pi r^2
  </code>.
</p>{% endset %}

{% set numberedExample %}<code data-math="numbered" id="eq-energy"
  data-mathml="<math display='block'><mi>E</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>m</mi><msup><mi>c</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math>">
  E = mc^2
</code>

<p>See <a href="#eq-energy">Equation 1</a>.</p>{% endset %}

{% set copyableExample %}<code data-math="copyable"
  data-mathml="<math display='block'><msubsup><mo>&int;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>&infin;</mo></msubsup><msup><mi>e</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></msup><mi>d</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><msqrt><mi>&pi;</mi></msqrt><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>">
  \int_0^\infty e^{-x^2} dx = \frac{\sqrt{\pi}}{2}
</code>{% endset %}

{% set markdownExample %}{% raw %}```math
x = \frac{-b \pm \sqrt{b^2 - 4ac}}{2a}
```{% endraw %}{% endset %}

{% set markdownOutputExample %}<pre><code class="language-math">
  x = \frac{-b \pm \sqrt{b^2 - 4ac}}{2a}
</code></pre>{% endset %}

{% set eventExample %}{% raw %}const el = document.querySelector('[data-math]');

el.addEventListener('math:rendered', (e) => {
  console.log('LaTeX:', e.detail.latex);
  console.log('Inline:', e.detail.inline);
  console.log('Number:', e.detail.number);
});{% endraw %}{% endset %}

{% set dynamicExample %}const code = document.createElement('code');
code.dataset.math = 'inline';
code.dataset.mathml = '<math><mi>x</mi></math>';
code.textContent = 'x';
document.body.appendChild(code);
// Auto-enhanced via MutationObserver{% endset %}

{% set noJsExample %}<code data-math>E = mc^2</code>
<!-- Without data-mathml, the LaTeX source displays as readable code -->{% endset %}

<section>
    <h2>Overview</h2>
    <p>The <code>data-math</code> attribute enhances <code>&lt;code&gt;</code> elements with precompiled MathML. The original LaTeX source stays readable without JavaScript, and when JS runs, it is replaced by rendered MathML.</p>

    <browser-window
      src="/docs/examples/demos/data-math-basic.html"
      url="https://vanilla-breeze.dev/data-math"
      title="data-math Enhancement"
      shadow>
    </browser-window>

    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Block math with precompiled MathML">{{ blockExample | escape }}</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>How It Works</h2>
    <ol>
      <li>Add <code>data-math</code> to a <code>&lt;code&gt;</code> element with LaTeX source as its text content</li>
      <li>Add <code>data-mathml</code> with the precompiled MathML string</li>
      <li>On page load, the script reads <code>data-mathml</code>, injects a <code>&lt;math&gt;</code> element, and hides the original <code>&lt;code&gt;</code></li>
      <li>Without <code>data-mathml</code>, the LaTeX source displays as-is &mdash; readable fallback with no JS dependency</li>
    </ol>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Attributes</h2>
    <table class="props-table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Attribute</th>
          <th>Type</th>
          <th>Description</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td><code>data-math</code></td>
          <td>token list</td>
          <td>Space-separated tokens: <code>inline</code>, <code>numbered</code>, <code>copyable</code>. An empty value defaults to block rendering.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>data-mathml</code></td>
          <td>string</td>
          <td>Precompiled MathML string to inject. Without this, the element shows the raw LaTeX source.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>data-math-state</code></td>
          <td>string</td>
          <td>Set automatically: <code>"rendered"</code> when MathML injected, <code>"source"</code> when showing raw LaTeX.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>data-math-init</code></td>
          <td>boolean</td>
          <td>Set automatically to prevent double-binding. Do not set manually.</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Tokens</h2>
    <table class="props-table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Token</th>
          <th>Description</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td><code>inline</code></td>
          <td>Renders inline math, wrapping in a <code>&lt;span&gt;</code> instead of a <code>&lt;div&gt;</code>.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>numbered</code></td>
          <td>Auto-increments the equation counter and displays a number. Registers in <code>window.VBMath.equations</code> if the element has an <code>id</code>.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>copyable</code></td>
          <td>Clicking the rendered math copies the original LaTeX source to the clipboard with a screen reader announcement.</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Inline Math</h2>
    <p>Use the <code>inline</code> token for math that flows within paragraph text.</p>

    <div class="example">
      <p>The area is
        <code data-math="inline"
          data-mathml="<math><mi>&pi;</mi><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math>">
          \pi r^2
        </code>.
      </p>
    </div>

    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Inline math">{{ inlineExample | escape }}</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Numbered Equations</h2>
    <p>Combine <code>numbered</code> with an <code>id</code> for linkable, numbered equations.</p>

    <div class="example">
      <code data-math="numbered" id="eq-energy-demo"
        data-mathml="<math display='block'><mi>E</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>m</mi><msup><mi>c</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math>">
        E = mc^2
      </code>
    </div>

    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Numbered equation">{{ numberedExample | escape }}</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Copyable Math</h2>
    <p>The <code>copyable</code> token adds a click-to-copy interaction. Clicking copies the LaTeX source to the clipboard and announces it to screen readers.</p>

    <div class="example">
      <code data-math="copyable"
        data-mathml="<math display='block'><msubsup><mo>&int;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>&infin;</mo></msubsup><msup><mi>e</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></msup><mi>d</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><msqrt><mi>&pi;</mi></msqrt><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>">
        \int_0^\infty e^{-x^2} dx = \frac{\sqrt{\pi}}{2}
      </code>
    </div>

    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Copyable math">{{ copyableExample | escape }}</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Markdown Integration</h2>
    <p>Markdown processors emit <code>code.language-math</code> for fenced math blocks. The enhancement script auto-detects these &mdash; no extra configuration needed.</p>

    <code-block language="markdown" show-lines label="Markdown source">{{ markdownExample | escape }}</code-block>

    <p>This produces the standard HTML output:</p>

    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Emitted HTML">{{ markdownOutputExample | escape }}</code-block>

    <p>The <code>code.language-math</code> selector is matched automatically alongside <code>[data-math]</code>. For precompiled MathML, add <code>data-mathml</code> to the element at build time via a Remark or Markdown-it plugin.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Events</h2>
    <table class="props-table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Event</th>
          <th>Detail</th>
          <th>Description</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td><code>math:rendered</code></td>
          <td><code>{ latex, inline, number }</code></td>
          <td>Fired after MathML is injected. <code>latex</code> is the source text, <code>inline</code> is a boolean, <code>number</code> is the equation number (or null).</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <code-block language="javascript" show-lines label="Listening for math:rendered">{{ eventExample | escape }}</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Progressive Enhancement</h2>
    <p>Without <code>data-mathml</code>, the LaTeX source displays as a readable <code>&lt;code&gt;</code> block. This is the no-JS fallback:</p>

    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="No-JS fallback">{{ noJsExample | escape }}</code-block>

    <p>The element receives <code>data-math-state="source"</code> so you can style the fallback state differently if needed.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Dynamic Content</h2>
    <p>Elements added to the DOM after page load are automatically enhanced via a MutationObserver. No manual initialization needed.</p>

    <code-block language="javascript" show-lines label="Dynamically added math">{{ dynamicExample | escape }}</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Accessibility</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>The injected <code>&lt;math&gt;</code> element is natively understood by screen readers (VoiceOver, NVDA)</li>
      <li>The original LaTeX source is preserved in the DOM as hidden fallback content</li>
      <li>Copy confirmation uses <code>aria-live="polite"</code> for screen reader announcements</li>
      <li>Numbered equations are linkable via <code>id</code> and standard <code>&lt;a href&gt;</code></li>
    </ul>
  </section>
